 <h2>Controlling Your Pet</h2><br><br><br>Controlling your pet is vital to being a good mage, there are a few simple commands you need to know:<br><br><br><br>Firstly, tell it when to follow you:<br><br> <i>/pet follow me</i> - Tells the pet to follow you.<br><br> <i>/pet sit</i> - Tells the pet to stay where it is.<br><br> <i>/pet guard here</i> - Like /pet sit, except that the pet will always return to that position when its not fighting, until /pet follow me is used.<br><br><br><br>Now telling it to kill stuff:<br><br> <i>/pet kill</i> - Tells your pet to attack your current target.<br><br> <i>/pet back</i> - Tells your pet to back off and stop attacking.<br><br> <i>/pet hold</i> - THIS IS ONLY AVAILABLE AS THE RESULT OF AN AA ABILITY: Tells your pet to back off, and it will never attack unless specifically told to.<br><br><br>Other stuff:<br><br> <i>/pet health</i> - Your pet will tell you its health state.<br><br> <i>/pet who leader</i> - Your pet will say "My leader is <name>". Not very useful, but still.<br><br> <i>/pet get lost</i> - Dismisses your pet<br><br> <i>/pet taunt on</i> - Turns your pets taunting on<br><br> <i>/pet taunt off</i> - Turns your pets taunting off<br><br><br><br></center><b><u>Comments/Feedback:</u></b><br><br>
